    "recap_headline": "Fresno State Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif.\n\u2013 The Fresno State baseball team dropped a midweek contest to Cal Poly, 13\u20133, on Tuesday evening at Baggett Stadium.\nThe Bulldogs recorded seven hits in the game and built an early lead, but the Mustangs broke the game open in the middle innings to pull away. Fresno State moved to 7\u20138 on the season with the loss.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nAfter a scoreless first inning, Fresno State struck first in the second. The Bulldogs pushed across two runs to take an early advantage, with\nMarcus Nolen\ndriving in a run and\nSky Collins\nlater adding an RBI to give Fresno State a 2\u20130 lead.\nCal Poly responded in the bottom half of the inning to trim the deficit, but the Bulldogs added another run in the third inning to extend the lead to 3\u20131.\nGriffen Sotomayor\nand\nJett Ruby\nhelped spark the offense early as Fresno State collected multiple hits through the first three innings.\nThe Mustangs seized control beginning in the third inning, stringing together hits to score multiple runs and flip the momentum. Cal Poly continued to capitalize on opportunities in the fourth and fifth innings, scoring in bunches to take a commanding lead. Fresno State's bullpen worked through the late innings to stabilize things, but the early surge by the Mustangs proved decisive.\nFresno State finished with three runs on seven hits while Cal Poly totaled 13 runs on 12 hits.\nNOTES\nFresno State totaled seven hits and drew three walks.\nSky Collins\nrecorded the Bulldogs' lone RBI hit with runners in scoring position.\nFresno State stole two bases in the game.\nUP NEXT\nThe Bulldogs will open conference play this weekend at home against preseason favorite Nevada. Game one is set for Friday at 6:05 p.m. PT."
